They turned suddenly to the voice, and saw a man in blue robes riding up from down the path.  He had short whiteblond hair and steely greyblue eyes.  A spellbook was ctucked under his arm.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cedric!&quot; Menion cried joyfully.<br>
<br>
&quot;Heya, Menion,&quot; he waved, climbing down from his steed.  &quot;I missed ya! The minute I arrived at the Tavern, Mitzi told me you'd gone! What happened?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, nothing much,&quot; he shrugged, as his gaze went to Kyonae.  &quot;So, what did you mean, she's right.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, she's quite right in believing that.&quot;  He cleared his throat matter of factly.  &quot;I've read up on things, and Kuja Dracolon is the current commander in Osiria.  And by what Kyonae has said, he's following a basic strategy plan used by the Lorelonians against Milonia in the Siren War.  He's taking the Temple as his base, and probably if he doesn't get what he wants, he'll...um...he'll destroy it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Bullshit!&quot; Ember shouted.  &quot;There is no way in hell they're taking down THAT temple!  C'mon, Menion, we gotta go save it!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Calm down, Ember,&quot; Menion urged.  &quot;We don't even know where we are.  how are we supposed to find the Temple of Firadra?&quot;<br>
   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cliffaro@collisionworld>Cliffaro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(3/7/03 12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm147.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Search</span><hr size=1> Mirak took in all the information he was being given and quickly processed it. &quot;Now that we know who this commander is and where he can be found let us make our way at once.&quot; <br>
Mirak quickly summoned a portal. &quot;If memory serves the Temple of Firadra was busy being constructed when the Void Demons ruled this world so it should still be in the Unknown Regions?&quot;<br>
